The paper discusses models for games of incomplete information, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The use of graphical models suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), while the discussion of causal dependence structure suggests a connection to causal inference and causal graphical models (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of signals and information, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS).
